# CC PROMPT — v2.44.5 — fix(tests): move TestCase + TEST_CASES into api/db/test_definitions.py

## What this does

The root problem: `tests_api.py` imports `TEST_CASES` from `tests/integration/test_agent.py`,
which lives under `tests/` — a directory that has been excluded from the container
by `.dockerignore` in various forms across multiple fix attempts. The 500 persists
because no amount of `.dockerignore` tweaking guarantees the tests/ tree lands in
the right place.

Permanent fix: move the test case dataclass and TEST_CASES list into `api/db/test_definitions.py`,
which is always in the container (it's inside `api/`). Then:
- `tests_api.py` imports from `api.db.test_definitions` (always works in container)
- `tests/integration/test_agent.py` imports `TestCase` and `TEST_CASES` from there too
  (backward-compatible — CLI tests still work)

